import React, { useEffect, useRef, useState } from "react";

// MediaPipe Í≥µÏãù Î¨∏ÏÑú Í∏∞Ï§Ä Îàà ÎûúÎìúÎßàÌÅ¨ Ïù∏Îç±Ïä§
const EYE_LEFT = [263, 249, 390, 373, 374, 380];
const EYE_RIGHT = [33, 7, 163, 144, 145, 153];

function calculateEAR(landmarks, eyeIndices) {
  const [p1, p2, p3, p4, p5, p6] = eyeIndices.map((i) => landmarks[i]);
  const vertical1 = Math.hypot(p2.x - p6.x, p2.y - p6.y);
  const vertical2 = Math.hypot(p3.x - p5.x, p3.y - p5.y);
  const horizontal = Math.hypot(p1.x - p4.x, p1.y - p4.y);
  return (vertical1 + vertical2) / (2 * horizontal);
}

const EAR_THRESHOLD = 0.25;
const CONSEC_FRAMES = 3;

const ViewCamera = () => {
  const videoRef = useRef(null);
  const [blinkCount, setBlinkCount] = useState(0);
  const [ear, setEar] = useState(0);
  const [frameCounter, setFrameCounter] = useState(0);
  const [isInitialized, setIsInitialized] = useState(false);

  useEffect(() => {
    let faceMesh = null;
    let animationFrameId = null;
    let script = null;

    const initializeMediaPipe = async () => {
      // 1. MediaPipe UMD Î≤ÑÏ†Ñ Î°úÎìú
      await new Promise((resolve) => {
        script = document.createElement("script");
        script.src =
          "https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/face_mesh/face_mesh.js";
        script.onload = resolve;
        document.head.appendChild(script);
      });

      // 2. WASM ÌååÏùº Í≤ΩÎ°ú ÏßÄÏ†ï (Ï§ëÏöî!)
      window.Module = {
        locateFile: (path) =>
          `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/face_mesh/${path}`,
      };

      // 3. FaceMesh Ïù∏Ïä§ÌÑ¥Ïä§ ÏÉùÏÑ±
      faceMesh = new window.FaceMesh({
        locateFile: (file) =>
          `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@mediapipe/face_mesh/${file}`,
      });

      faceMesh.setOptions({
        maxNumFaces: 1,
        refineLandmarks: true,
        minDetectionConfidence: 0.5,
        minTrackingConfidence: 0.5,
        selfieMode: true,
      });

      faceMesh.onResults((results) => {
        if (results.multiFaceLandmarks?.[0]) {
          const landmarks = results.multiFaceLandmarks[0];
          const leftEAR = calculateEAR(landmarks, EYE_LEFT);
          const rightEAR = calculateEAR(landmarks, EYE_RIGHT);
          const avgEAR = (leftEAR + rightEAR) / 2;
          setEar(avgEAR);

          if (avgEAR < EAR_THRESHOLD) {
            setFrameCounter((prev) => prev + 1);
          } else {
            if (frameCounter >= CONSEC_FRAMES) {
              setBlinkCount((prev) => prev + 1);
            }
            setFrameCounter(0);
          }
        }
      });

      // 4. ÌîÑÎ†àÏûÑ Ï≤òÎ¶¨ Î£®ÌîÑ
      const processFrame = async () => {
        if (videoRef.current?.readyState === 4) {
          try {
            await faceMesh.send({ image: videoRef.current });
          } catch (error) {
            console.error("ÌîÑÎ†àÏûÑ Ï≤òÎ¶¨ Ïò§Î•ò:", error);
          }
        }
        animationFrameId = requestAnimationFrame(processFrame);
      };

      processFrame();
      setIsInitialized(true);
    };

    initializeMediaPipe().catch(console.error);

    return () => {
      if (animationFrameId) cancelAnimationFrame(animationFrameId);
      if (faceMesh) faceMesh.close();
      if (script) document.head.removeChild(script);
    };
  }, []);

  // ÏõπÏ∫† Ïó∞Í≤∞
  useEffect(() => {
    if (!isInitialized) return;
    const constraints = {
      video: {
        width: { ideal: 640 },
        height: { ideal: 480 },
        facingMode: "user",
        frameRate: { ideal: 30 },
      },
    };
    navigator.mediaDevices
      .getUserMedia(constraints)
      .then((stream) => {
        if (videoRef.current) {
          videoRef.current.srcObject = stream;
          videoRef.current.onloadedmetadata = () => {
            videoRef.current.play().catch(console.error);
          };
        }
      })
      .catch((err) => {
        alert("ÏõπÏ∫† Ï†ëÍ∑º Ïò§Î•ò: " + err.message);
      });
  }, [isInitialized]);

  return (
    <div
      style={{
        position: "relative",
        width: "100%",
        maxWidth: 640,
        margin: "0 auto",
        backgroundColor: "#1a1a1a",
        borderRadius: "10px",
        overflow: "hidden",
      }}
    >
      <video
        ref={videoRef}
        autoPlay
        playsInline
        style={{
          width: "100%",
          height: "auto",
          transform: "scaleX(-1)", // ÎØ∏Îü¨ Î™®Îìú
        }}
      />
      <div
        style={{
          position: "absolute",
          top: 20,
          left: 20,
          color: "#fff",
          backgroundColor: "rgba(0,0,0,0.7)",
          padding: "10px 20px",
          borderRadius: 8,
          boxShadow: "0 2px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.3)",
        }}
      >
        <div style={{ fontSize: 18, marginBottom: 5 }}>
          üëÅÔ∏è Blink Count: <strong>{blinkCount}</strong>
        </div>
        <div style={{ fontSize: 14 }}>
          EAR: {ear.toFixed(3)} (Threshold: {EAR_THRESHOLD})
        </div>
      </div>
      {ear < EAR_THRESHOLD && (
        <div
          style={{
            position: "absolute",
            top: "50%",
            left: "50%",
            transform: "translate(-50%, -50%)",
            fontSize: "2em",
            fontWeight: "bold",
            color: "#ff4444",
            textShadow: "0 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.5)",
            animation: "blink 1s infinite",
          }}
        >
          BLINKING!
        </div>
      )}
      <style>{`
        @keyframes blink {
          0% { opacity: 1; }
          50% { opacity: 0.3; }
          100% { opacity: 1; }
        }
      `}</style>
    </div>
  );
};

export default ViewCamera;
